"We need"? Yes.

44
00:06:17,503 --> 00:06:18,663
Well, what about you need?

45
00:06:18,755 --> 00:06:19,755
I need?

46
00:06:19,839 --> 00:06:22,046
I don't know what you're talking about.

47
00:06:22,508 --> 00:06:23,918
You probably don't.

48
00:06:24,177 --> 00:06:26,008
And what precisely
am I supposed to know?

49
00:06:26,304 --> 00:06:27,544
Come onl!

50
00:06:27,639 --> 00:06:29,879
You want me to stay
because of the way you feel about me.

51
00:06:29,933 --> 00:06:32,640
Yes! You're a great help to us.
You're a natural leader.

52
00:06:32,727 --> 00:06:35,389
No! That's not it.

53
00:06:35,480 --> 00:06:36,811
Come on.

54
00:06:37,315 --> 00:06:38,600
A-ha

55
00:06:38,691 --> 00:06:40,127
- come on.
- You're imagining things.

56
00:06:40,151 --> 00:06:41,937
Am 1? Then why are you following me?

57
00:06:42,028 --> 00:06:44,610
Afraid I was gonna leave
without giving you a good-bye kiss?

58
00:06:44,697 --> 00:06:45,799
I'd just as soon kiss a wookiee!

59
00:06:45,823 --> 00:06:47,108
I can arrange that.

60
00:06:47,283 --> 00:06:49,274
You could use a good kiss!

61
00:06:50,536 --> 00:06:51,680
C-3pqo: Don't try to blame me.

62
00:06:51,704 --> 00:06:53,390
I didn't ask you to turn on
the thermal heater.

63
00:06:53,414 --> 00:06:56,372
I merely commented that it was freezing
in the Princess' chamber.

64
00:06:56,459 --> 00:06:58,745
But it's supposed to be freezing.

65
00:06:58,836 --> 00:07:01,356
How we're going to dry out
all her clothes, I really don't know.

66
00:07:01,714 --> 00:07:03,124
Oh, switch off!

67
00:07:03,216 --> 00:07:04,276
Why did you take this apart now?

68
00:07:04,300 --> 00:07:06,195
I'm trying to get us out of here,
and you pull both...

69
00:07:06,219 --> 00:07:07,219
Excuse me, sir.

70
00:07:07,303 --> 00:07:08,364
Put them back together now!

71
00:07:08,388 --> 00:07:09,924
Might I have a word with you, please?

72
00:07:10,014 --> 00:07:11,659
What do you want?
“Well, it's Princess Leia, sir.

73
00:07:11,683 --> 00:07:13,327
She's been trying to get you
on the communicator.

74
00:07:13,351 --> 00:07:15,216
I turned it off.
I don't want to talk to her.

75
00:07:15,311 --> 00:07:17,677
Well, Princess Leia
is wondering about master Luke.

76
00:07:17,772 --> 00:07:19,458
He hasn't come back yet.
She doesn't know where he is.

77
00:07:19,482 --> 00:07:21,585
- I don't know where he is.
- Nobody knows where he is.

78
00:07:21,609 --> 00:07:22,940
What do you mean, nobody knows?

79
00:07:23,027 --> 00:07:24,938
- Well, uh, you see...
- Deck officer!

80
00:07:25,029 --> 00:07:26,894
- Deck officer!
- Excuse me, sir, might I...

81
00:07:26,990 --> 00:07:28,050
Deck off. Officer: Yes, sir?
As, sir?

82
00:07:28,074 --> 00:07:29,551
Do you know
where commander Skywalker is?

83
00:07:29,575 --> 00:07:30,575
I haven't seen him.

84
00:07:30,660 --> 00:07:32,346
It's possible he came in through
the south entrance.

85
00:07:32,370 --> 00:07:34,827
"It's possible™?
Why don't you go find out?

86
00:07:34,914 --> 00:07:36,034
It's getting dark out there.

87
00:07:36,082 --> 00:07:37,322
Yes, sir.

88
00:07:37,458 --> 00:07:39,574
Excuse me, sir.
Might I inquire what's going on?

89
00:07:39,669 --> 00:07:40,784
Why not?

90
00:07:41,045 --> 00:07:42,160
Impossible man.

91
00:07:42,255 --> 00:07:44,041
Come along, r2,
let's find Princess Leia.

92
00:07:44,132 --> 00:07:47,545
Between ourselves, I think
master Luke is in considerable danger.

93
00:07:57,228 --> 00:07:59,456
Sir, commander Skywalker
hasn't come in the south entrance.

94
00:07:59,480 --> 00:08:00,749
He might have forgotten to check in.

95
00:08:00,773 --> 00:08:01,917
Not likely. Are the speeders ready?

96
00:08:01,941 --> 00:08:04,301
Uh, not yet. We're having trouble
adapting them to the cold.

97
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:05,504
We'll have to go out on tauntauns.

98
00:08:05,528 --> 00:08:07,268
Sir, the temperature's
dropping too rapidly.

99
00:08:07,363 --> 00:08:08,923
That's right,
and my friend's out in it.

100
00:08:14,037 --> 00:08:16,557
Deck officer: Your tauntaun will freeze
before you reach the first marker.

101
00:08:16,581 --> 00:08:18,572
Then I'll see you in hell. Hyah!

102
00:10:36,679 --> 00:10:38,419
C-3p0o: You must come along now, r2.

103
00:10:38,514 --> 00:10:40,550
There's really nothing more we can do.

104
00:10:40,641 --> 00:10:42,848
And my joints are freezing up.

105
00:10:44,020 --> 00:10:45,430
Don't say things like that!

106
00:10:45,521 --> 00:10:47,041
Of course we'll see master Luke again.

107
00:10:48,107 --> 00:10:50,473
And he'll be quite all right.
You'll see.

108
00:10:50,568 --> 00:10:52,433
Stupid little short circuit.

109
00:10:52,862 --> 00:10:54,477
He'll be quite all right.

110
00:11:52,171 --> 00:11:54,162
Sir, all the patrols are in.

111
00:11:54,257 --> 00:11:55,257
Still no...

112
00:11:56,467 --> 00:11:58,958
Still no contact from Skywalker or solo.

113
00:11:59,387 --> 00:12:02,800
Mistress Leia, r2 says he's been
quite unable to pick up any signals,

114
00:12:03,224 --> 00:12:05,510
although he does admit
that his own range

115
00:12:05,601 --> 00:12:07,057
is far too weak to abandon all hope.

116
00:12:07,144 --> 00:12:09,039
Your highness,
there's nothing more we can do tonight.

117
00:12:09,063 --> 00:12:11,475
The shield doors must be closed.

118
00:12:13,067 --> 00:12:14,067
Close the doors.

119
00:12:14,151 --> 00:12:15,151
Lieutenant: Yes, sir.

120
00:12:16,946 --> 00:12:21,360
R2 says the chances of survival
are 725 to 1.

121
00:12:33,045 --> 00:12:36,583
Actually, r2 has been known
to make mistakes...

122
00:12:39,593 --> 00:12:40,878
From time to time.

123
00:12:41,387 --> 00:12:42,752
Oh, dear. Oh, dear.

124
00:12:46,726 --> 00:12:47,869
Don't worry about master Luke.

125
00:12:47,893 --> 00:12:49,303
I'm sure he'll be all right.

126
00:12:49,395 --> 00:12:51,761
He's quite clever, you know,
for a human being.

127
00:13:07,997 --> 00:13:09,328
Man: Luke.

128
00:13:11,667 --> 00:13:12,952
Luke.

129
00:13:20,551 --> 00:13:21,961
Ben?

130
00:13:22,053 --> 00:13:24,760
You will go to the dagobah system.

131
00:13:25,306 --> 00:13:26,671
Dagobah system?

132
00:13:27,266 --> 00:13:29,848
There you will learn from Yoda,

133
00:13:30,436 --> 00:13:33,519
the jedi master who instructed me.

134
00:13:35,107 --> 00:13:36,187
Ben!

135
00:13:36,859 --> 00:13:37,859
Ben.

136
00:13:42,615 --> 00:13:43,946
Han: Luke!

137
00:13:44,325 --> 00:13:45,405
Luke!

138
00:13:52,541 --> 00:13:54,452
Don't do this, Luke.

139
00:13:54,543 --> 00:13:56,454
Come on, give me a sign here.

140
00:14:19,610 --> 00:14:21,396
Not much time.

141
00:14:21,487 --> 00:14:22,647
Ben.

142
00:14:22,738 --> 00:14:24,103
Ben.

143
00:14:28,744 --> 00:14:30,405
Hang on, kid.

144
00:14:31,580 --> 00:14:34,492
- Dagobah system. Dagobah.
- Han: Whew!

145
00:14:34,583 --> 00:14:36,323
This may smell bad, kid...

146
00:14:37,169 --> 00:14:39,160
Yoda.

147
00:14:39,588 --> 00:14:41,328
But it'll keep you warm...

148
00:14:41,674 --> 00:14:43,835
Till I get the shelter up.

149
00:14:43,926 --> 00:14:46,212
Ben... dagobah...

150
00:14:46,303 --> 00:14:48,009
Ahhh!

151
00:14:48,556 --> 00:14:53,300
Ah! I thought they smelled bad
on the outside!

152
00:15:36,979 --> 00:15:39,971
Echo base, I've got something.

153
00:15:40,065 --> 00:15:41,585
Not much, but it could be a life form.

154
00:15:46,030 --> 00:15:48,237
Commander Skywalker, do you copy?

155
00:15:48,491 --> 00:15:50,152
This is rogue two.

156
00:15:50,534 --> 00:15:52,695
This is rogue two.

157
00:15:53,162 --> 00:15:56,279
Captain solo, do you copy?

158
00:16:01,921 --> 00:16:05,630
Commander Skywalker, do you copy?

159
00:16:05,716 --> 00:16:07,672
This is rogue two.

160
00:16:07,760 --> 00:16:10,547
Han: Good morning.
Nice of you guys to drop by.

161
00:16:11,722 --> 00:16:14,213
Echo base, this is rogue two.

162
00:16:14,308 --> 00:16:15,593
I've found them.

163
00:16:15,684 --> 00:16:17,345
Repeat, I've found them.

164
00:16:47,675 --> 00:16:50,792
Master Luke, sir, it's so good
to see you fully functional again.

165
00:16:50,886 --> 00:16:52,155
Luke: Thanks, 3po.

166
00:16:52,179 --> 00:16:53,885
C-3p0o: R2 expresses his relief also.

167
00:16:54,014 --> 00:16:56,801
How ya feelin', kid?
You don't look so bad to me.

168
00:16:57,768 --> 00:17:00,555
You look strong enough
to pull the ears off a gundark.

169
00:17:00,646 --> 00:17:02,182
Thanks to you.

170
00:17:02,273 --> 00:17:04,730
That's two you owe me, junior.
J j

171
00:17:05,025 --> 00:17:06,025
well, your worship,

172
00:17:06,110 --> 00:17:08,977
looks like you managed to keep me around
for a little while longer.

173
00:17:09,488 --> 00:17:11,149
I had nothing to do with it.

174
00:17:11,282 --> 00:17:14,274
General rieekan thinks it's dangerous
for any ships to leave the system

175
00:17:14,368 --> 00:17:15,928
until we've activated the energy field.

176
00:17:16,161 --> 00:17:17,321
Han: That's a good story.

177
00:17:17,413 --> 00:17:18,949
I think you just can't bear to let

178
00:17:19,039 --> 00:17:21,371
a gorgeous guy like me
out of your sight.

179
00:17:22,251 --> 00:17:25,038
I don't know where
you get your delusions, laser brain.

180
00:17:28,299 --> 00:17:30,210
Laugh it up, fuzzball,

181
00:17:30,718 --> 00:17:33,585
but you didn't see us alone
in the south passage.

182
00:17:33,929 --> 00:17:36,136
She expressed her true feelings for me.

183
00:17:37,683 --> 00:17:40,641
Why, you stuck-up, half-witted,

184
00:17:41,020 --> 00:17:43,386
scruffy-looking nerf herder!

185
00:17:44,648 --> 00:17:46,354
Who's scruffy-looking?

186
00:17:49,737 --> 00:17:51,047
I must have hit
pretty close to the Mark

187
00:17:51,071 --> 00:17:53,062
to get her all riled up like that,
huh, kid?

188
00:17:56,702 --> 00:17:59,364
Well, I guess you don't know
everything about women yet,

189
00:18:05,711 --> 00:18:08,498
Man on pa: Headquarters personnel,
report to command center.

190
00:18:11,467 --> 00:18:14,630
Headquarters personnel,
report to command center.

191
00:18:14,720 --> 00:18:15,720
Take it easy.

192
00:18:16,472 --> 00:18:17,712
Excuse us, please.

193
00:18:21,226 --> 00:18:23,308
Princess, we have a visitor.

194
00:18:24,313 --> 00:18:27,100
Picked up something
outside the base's zone 12 moving east.

195
00:18:27,191 --> 00:18:28,191
It's metal.

196
00:18:28,275 --> 00:18:29,586
Then it couldn't be
one of those creatures.

197
00:18:29,610 --> 00:18:31,191
Could be a speeder, one of ours.

198
00:18:31,278 --> 00:18:32,484
No.

199
00:18:32,571 --> 00:18:33,606
Wait.

200
00:18:33,697 --> 00:18:36,404
There's something
very weak coming through.

201
00:18:39,662 --> 00:18:42,745
Sir, I'm fluent in six million
forms of communication.

202
00:18:42,831 --> 00:18:44,431
This signal is not used by the alliance.

203
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:45,990
It could be an imperial code.

204
00:18:51,548 --> 00:18:52,859
It isn't friendly, whatever it is.

205
00:18:52,883 --> 00:18:54,323
Come on, Chewie, let's check it out.

206
00:18:54,385 --> 00:18:56,626
Send rogues 10 and 11 to station 38.

207
00:19:33,424 --> 00:19:34,609
Han over comlink:
I'm afraid there's not much left

208
00:19:34,633 --> 00:19:36,294
Leia: What was it?
Droid of some kind.

209
00:19:36,385 --> 00:19:38,671
I didn't hit it that hard,
must've had a self-destruct

210
00:19:39,179 --> 00:19:40,760
an imperial probe droid.

211
00:19:40,973 --> 00:19:43,715
It's a good bet the empire knows
we're here.

212
00:19:44,017 --> 00:19:45,882
We'd better start the evacuation.

213
00:20:31,023 --> 00:20:32,388
Piett: Admiral.

214
00:20:32,649 --> 00:20:33,764
Yes, captain?

215
00:20:35,110 --> 00:20:36,430
I think we've got something, sir.

216
00:20:36,987 --> 00:20:39,945
The report is only a fragment
from a probe droid in the hoth system,

217
00:20:40,032 --> 00:20:41,397
but it's the best lead we've had.

218
00:20:41,492 --> 00:20:44,484
We have thousands of probe droids
searching the galaxy.

219
00:20:44,578 --> 00:20:45,658
I want proof, not leads.

220
00:20:45,746 --> 00:20:47,611
Piett:
The visuals indicate life readings.

221
00:20:47,706 --> 00:20:50,018
Ozzel.: It could mean anything.
If we followed up every lead...

222
00:20:50,042 --> 00:20:52,875
But, sir, the hoth system
is supposed to be devoid of humans.

223
00:20:52,961 --> 00:20:54,397
Darth Vader: You've found something?

224
00:20:54,421 --> 00:20:55,536
Yes, my lord.

225
00:20:57,925 --> 00:21:00,337
That's it. The rebels are there.

226
00:21:01,011 --> 00:21:04,970
My lord, there are so many
uncharted settlements.

227
00:21:05,057 --> 00:21:06,057
It could be smugglers...

228
00:21:06,141 --> 00:21:07,677
That is the system.

229
00:21:07,768 --> 00:21:10,305
And I'm sure Skywalker is with them.
Y

230
00:21:10,562 --> 00:21:12,928
set your course for the hoth system.

231
00:21:13,148 --> 00:21:15,309
General veers, prepare your men.

232
00:21:15,901 --> 00:21:17,141
Admiral.

233
00:21:23,909 --> 00:21:26,446
Groups 7 and 10 will stay behind
to fly the speeders.

234
00:21:26,537 --> 00:21:27,993
As soon as each transport is loaded,

235
00:21:28,080 --> 00:21:30,391
